To build, run:

chmod +x build.sh
./build.sh

`build.sh` uses BuildKit when possible, otherwise falls
back on the classic builder. Failed builds automatically
prune cache/images so disk does not keep growing.

Manual build (no auto-cleanup on failure):

docker build -t code-server-image .

If you still run out of space:

df -h
docker system df
./build.sh # failed builds prune cache automatically
docker system prune -af
docker builder prune -af
